header":"He helped found a transatlantic steamship line","body":"An explorer and writer, Roosevelt co-founded the Roosevelt Steamship Company, which became part of the United States Lines. He published books on hunting and travel.","number":2},{"category":"character","header":"He kept his father alive on the Amazon","body":"On the 1914 expedition down Brazil's River of Doubt, Kermit rationed his own quinine to his malarial father and was credited with saving the former President's life. He nearly died of the fever himself.","number":3},{"category":"military","header":"He won the Military Cross in Mesopotamia","body":"In 1917 he took an honorary captaincy in the British Army and fought under General Maude in the Mesopotamian campaign, where he earned the Military Cross. He crossed to the American artillery in France for the war's last offensive.","number":4},{"category":"education","header":"He tore through Harvard in record time","body":"A voracious reader, he compressed the four-year Harvard course into about two and a half years, breaking off after his freshman year to join his father's African safari. He took his degree in 1912.","number":5}],"sources":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST002","relationship":"alumnus"},{"institution_id":"INST062","relationship":"alumnus"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"HD6126","display_label":"re-ran the River of Doubt eight decades later"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Kermit","last_name":"Roosevelt","display_name":"Kermit Roosevelt","gender":"male","bio_blurb":"Explorer, soldier, son of Theodore Roosevelt"},"military_service":[{"war":"World War I","branch":"British Army","rank":"Captain (honorary)","unit":"14th Light Armored Motor Battery, Machine Gun Corps","awards":"Military Cross","notes":"Served under General Maude in the Mesopotamian campaign, 1917-1918."},{"war":"World War I","branch":"United States Army","rank":"Captain","unit":"Battery C, 7th Field Artillery, 1st Division","notes":"Transferred to the American Expeditionary Force in France, 1918; Meuse-Argonne Offensive."},{"war":"World War II","branch":"United States Army","rank":"Major","unit":"Fort Richardson, Alaska","notes":"Intelligence officer; helped raise a territorial militia of Alaska Natives."}],"career":[{"role":"Explorer","organization":"Africa and South America"},{"role":"Assistant Manager","organization":"National City Bank, Buenos Aires","start_year":1914,"end_year":1916},{"role":"Founder","organization":"Roosevelt Steamship Company"},{"role":"Vice President","organization":"New York Zoological Society","start_year":1937,"end_year":1939},{"role":"Author","organization":"explorer-memoirist"}],"birth":{"year":1889,"country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1943,"country":"United States","city":"Anchorage","state":"Alaska"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM773"},"education":[{"institution_id":"INST062"},{"institution_id":"INST002","dates":"1912","type":"graduation","notes":"A.B."}],"number_of_marriages":1,"slug":"kermit-roosevelt-1889"},"HD6101":{"id":"HD6101","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"male","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"generation_from_thomas":11},"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["politics"],"notable_blurb":"CIA officer who ran the 1953 Iran coup","primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kermit_Roosevelt_Jr.","primary_url_label":"Wikipedia"},"parents":{"father_id":"HD6087","mother_id":"I01660"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I01661","children_ids":["HD6105"],"marriage_number":1,"marriage_year":1937}],"tags":["spy","author","harvard_graduate"],"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"career","header":"He ran the CIA's 1953 Iran coup","body":"Operating under a cover name, Kim Roosevelt orchestrated Operation Ajax, the CIA-British plot that overthrew Iran's prime minister and restored the Shah in 1953. Decades later he broke Agency tradition by publishing a book on how it was done.","number":1},{"category":"politics","header":"He refused to repeat the trick in Guatemala","body":"Asked to engineer a second coup in Guatemala in 1954, Roosevelt declined, judging that Iran had worked only because so many Iranians shared its aims. He left the Agency a few years later for the oil and defense industries.","number":2}],"sources":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST002","relationship":"alumnus"},{"institution_id":"INST062","relationship":"alumnus"},{"institution_id":"INST166","relationship":"officer"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD6093","display_label":"a Roosevelt cousin who ran CIA technical services"},{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD4700","display_label":"the general who ran Army intelligence in two wars"},{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"H00757","display_label":"Washington's spymaster who ran the Culper Ring"},{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD6115","display_label":"a cousin and fellow CIA Arabist officer"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Kermit","last_name":"Roosevelt","display_name":"Kermit \"Kim\" Roosevelt Jr.","gender":"male","bio_blurb":"CIA officer who ran the 1953 Iran coup","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780975235/28453409_127601744235_u75ojr.jpg","suffix":"Jr."},"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"History instructor","organization":"Caltech","start_year":1937,"end_year":1941},{"role":"Officer","organization":"Office of Strategic Services","start_year":1941,"end_year":1947},{"role":"Intelligence officer","organization":"Central Intelligence Agency","start_yea